JO  - Management Science
SP  - C-3
EP  - C-5
VL  - 12
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper presents a general model to be used in adjusting cash flows which occur over future time intervals to reflect the effects of continuous compounding and/or discounting. The method is illustrated by means of a hypothetical example. The framework of analysis employed here may be extended to other systems having similar characteristics of growth and decay.
AB  - This paper presents a general model to be used in adjusting cash flows which occur over future time intervals to reflect the effects of continuous compounding and/or discounting. The method is illustrated by means of a hypothetical example. The framework of analysis employed here may be extended to other systems having similar characteristics of growth and decay.
